      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of buying a house, is a trust account that holds funds for various expenses related to the property, such as property taxes and insurance. It's a way to ensure that these costs are paid on time, without having to worry about setting aside the funds yourself. You don't want to be stuck with a big tax bill or insurance premium, just like a homeowner would be stuck with a bunch of unwanted, uninvited guests - you know, like a group of mischievous goblins who love to cause trouble and make a mess. In Toronto, it's common for buyers to set up an escrow account, especially since property taxes and insurance rates can be quite high. The escrow account will be managed by your realtor or a third-party escrow agent, and they'll make sure that the funds are disbursed according to the agreed-upon schedule.",
